.\" Manpage for aimap.
.\" Contact security@d5data.ai or open an issue on github.com/Nicholas-Kloster/aimap
.TH AIMAP 1 "May 2026" "aimap 1.9.21" "Security Tools"

.SH NAME
aimap \- AI infrastructure scanner: find exposed LLMs, vector databases, ML model servers, agent platforms, and 100+ other AI/ML services

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B aimap
.RB [ \-target
.IR IP | HOSTNAME | CIDR ]
.RB [ \-list
.IR FILE ]
.RB [ \-ports
.IR LIST ]
.RB [ \-threads
.IR N ]
.RB [ \-timeout
.IR DURATION ]
.RB [ \-o
.IR FILE ]
.RB [ \-v ]
.RB [ \-scan-all-fingerprints ]
.RB [ \-exclude-compromised ]
.RB [ \-version ]

.SH DESCRIPTION
.B aimap
is a purpose-built scanner for AI and machine learning infrastructure. Where
.BR nmap (1)
and
.BR nuclei (1)
identify that a service is running, aimap identifies
.I which AI/ML service
is running and whether it is exposing data, PII, credentials, or compute.
.PP
Defenders run aimap against their own networks to surface shadow AI before attackers do. NuClide research uses aimap as the fingerprint engine for population-scale exposure surveys against authorized targets, with case studies published at https://nuclide-research.com.
.PP
All probes are read-only HTTP GETs. aimap never writes, authenticates, or exploits. It is safe to run against production infrastructure you own.

.SH SCANNING PIPELINE
aimap operates in three phases:
.TP
.B Phase 1 \- Port discovery
Parallel TCP connect scan across the specified ports. The 42-port default list covers AI-service defaults including Ollama (11434), Qdrant (6333), ChromaDB (8000), Milvus (19530), MLflow (5000), Jupyter (8888), Ray (8265), Docker Registry (5000), Elasticsearch (9200), and a curated set of common non-standard ports observed in real-world surveys.
.TP
.B Phase 2 \- Service fingerprinting
For each open port, aimap matches against 120 built-in AI/ML service fingerprints using path and body signatures. Matches are conjunctive: every condition in a probe's Matches[] must satisfy. Single-word body_contains matches are not allowed; signals must anchor to status code + JSON shape + body to be sound at population scale.
.TP
.B Phase 3 \- Deep enumeration
50 service-specific enumerators inspect schemas, collections, models, experiments, registries, and configuration to surface actionable findings (PII fields, unauthenticated RCE, credential exposure, claimable admin states). A cross-cutting credential scanner extracts vendor API keys (Langfuse, Helicone, Stripe, Anthropic, LangSmith, OpenRouter, Slack) from response bodies independent of the host's primary service. An ML-adjacency rule reports data-tier ports (Postgres, Redis, MinIO, Kafka, RabbitMQ) on hosts with confirmed AI/ML services.

.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-target " " \fIIP|HOSTNAME|CIDR\fR
Single target to scan. Accepts an IPv4 address, hostname, or CIDR block (e.g.,
.IR 10.0.0.0/24 ).
.TP
.BR \-list " " \fIFILE\fR
Path to a file containing targets, one per line. Lines starting with
.B #
are treated as comments and ignored.
.TP
.BR \-ports " " \fILIST\fR
Comma-separated list of ports to scan. Default 42-port list:
.I 80,443,1984,2379,3000,3001,4000,4040,4200,5000,5001,5678,6333,7575,7576,7860,8000,8001,8080,8081,8088,8123,8233,8265,8443,8501,8787,8888,8889,9000,9090,9091,9200,10000,11434,15500,18080,18789,19530,30000,51000,55000
.TP
.BR \-threads " " \fIN\fR
Number of concurrent scan goroutines. Default:
.BR 20 .
Internal-network scans typically benefit from 50-100. External scans should stay at 10-20 to avoid tripping rate limits or alerting.
.TP
.BR \-timeout " " \fIDURATION\fR
Per-connection timeout. Default:
.BR 5s .
Reduce to 2-3s on low-latency internal networks; increase to 10s for external scans.
.TP
.BR \-o " " \fIFILE\fR
Write a full JSON report to
.IR FILE .
Machine-readable output suitable for CI/CD integration or diffing across scans.
.TP
.B \-v
Verbose output. Shows per-host match reasoning, which helps interpret unexpected findings.
.TP
.B \-scan-all-fingerprints
Probe every fingerprint against every open port, bypassing the DefaultPorts filter. Trades ~30x more requests for thorough coverage. Use when services may be on non-canonical ports.
.TP
.B \-exclude-compromised
Drop hosts classified as compromised-by-extortion (e.g. Meow-class wiped Elasticsearch with read_me index) from the JSON report. Use for disclosure-pipeline input.
.TP
.B \-version
Print the aimap version and exit.

