.SH RISK LEVELS
aimap computes a risk level per service based on findings:
.TP
.B critical
Exploitable now, no authentication required. Examples: unauthenticated Jupyter code execution, exposed Flowise credentials endpoint, Dify with unclaimed admin account, format-validated Anthropic/Langfuse/Stripe key in HTTP response.
.TP
.B high
Sensitive data accessible without authentication. Examples: vector database with PII fields exposed, Langfuse trace data readable, MLflow experiments accessible, Docker registry catalog enumerable.
.TP
.B medium
Information disclosure or misconfiguration. Examples: version leaks, CORS misconfiguration, service identified with empty data, credential pattern matched but format validation failed.
.TP
.B low
Service detected with minor issues. Examples: header disclosure, signup-open observability platform.
.TP
.B info
Service identified, authentication in place, no actionable findings.
.PP
Escalation rule: if authentication status is
.B none
and any finding is
.BR high ,
the overall risk is promoted to
.BR critical .

.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Scan a single internal host for AI services:
.B aimap \-target 10.1.2.3 \-v

.TP
Audit an entire internal /16 for shadow AI deployments:
.B aimap \-target 10.0.0.0/16 \-threads 100 \-timeout 3s \-o audit.json

.TP
Check a list of public-facing hosts for AI exposure:
.B aimap \-list public-ips.txt \-threads 10 \-timeout 10s \-o external.json \-v

.TP
CI/CD deployment gate (fail build on critical findings):
.B aimap \-target $DEPLOY_URL \-o check.json && jq '.enum_results[] | select(.risk_level == "critical")' check.json

.TP
Investigate a single suspected host with wide port coverage:
.B aimap \-target 10.5.5.5 \-v \-ports 8000,8080,8443,8888,9091,11434,6333,19530,5000,3000,7860,4000,51000,55000

.TP
Population survey with all fingerprints against every open port:
.B aimap \-list survey-targets.txt \-scan-all-fingerprints \-threads 100 \-o survey.json

.SH OUTPUT
aimap prints a color-coded terminal summary showing open ports, identified services, per-service findings, ML-adjacency observations, and an overall risk assessment.
.PP
With
.BR \-o ,
a complete JSON report is written containing:
.IP \(bu 2
Scan metadata (tool, version, target, duration, ports scanned)
.IP \(bu 2
Open ports with banner data
.IP \(bu 2
Identified services with version and match details
.IP \(bu 2
ML adjacencies (data-tier ports on hosts with confirmed AI services)
.IP \(bu 2
Deep enumeration results per service
.IP \(bu 2
Findings with severity, category, and remediation-relevant context
.IP \(bu 2
Aggregate summary counts

.SH AUTHORIZATION
aimap performs active scanning (TCP connections and HTTP probes). Only run it against systems you own or have explicit written authorization to test. Unauthorized scanning of third-party infrastructure may violate local computer-misuse laws.
.PP
For passive reconnaissance of external targets, use dedicated OSINT tools instead (Shodan, Censys, Certificate Transparency logs).

.SH FILES
No configuration files. All options are controlled via command-line flags.

.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Scan completed successfully (findings may still be present; check output).
.TP
.B 1
Invalid arguments or failure opening target list file.

